/* Fallback only: every registered instance has its own country-specific note below. */
"EU.NOTE.PROTECTED_AREA" = "Protected area (Natura 2000). Drone flight is restricted under national nature-protection law: usually a permit is required and it is often prohibited. Check the local rules before flying.";

"EU.NOTE.PROTECTED_AREA.AT" = "Natura 2000 site. Nature protection is state law in Austria, so nine different regimes apply. Drone flight is generally banned outright in national parks, and in a Naturschutzgebiet the general ban on disturbing wildlife can catch a drone even where Austro Control shows no zone. Permission comes from the state nature authority, whose fines are separate from Austro Control's.";
"EU.NOTE.PROTECTED_AREA.BE" = "Natura 2000 site. In Wallonia, flying a drone over any designated nature reserve is prohibited outright (Nature Conservation Law of 12 July 1973, art. 11, as amended in 2019), with fines up to 100,000 EUR. In Flanders, low flying over recognised reserves is prohibited (Natuurdecreet art. 35 §2 12°). skeyes publishes neither, so ask the reserve's manager before flying.";
"EU.NOTE.PROTECTED_AREA.NL" = "Natura 2000 site. Flying a drone here is in principle not permitted, because it can disturb protected species and habitats. Provincial ordinances set the detail, and an exemption needs an ecological assessment and usually a permit. Restrictions are strictest in the breeding season (roughly March to August).";
"EU.NOTE.PROTECTED_AREA.SE" = "Natura 2000 site. Drone flight inside a Natura 2000 area requires permission, and national parks are closed to drones entirely. Ordinary naturreservat carry no blanket ban: each has its own föreskrifter, so check the reserve's rules or ask the county board (länsstyrelsen).";

/* Grey footnote under a tap result, for countries that publish no residential geometry. */
"RESIDENTIAL.INFO.INTRO" = "Residential areas are not part of this country's drone dataset. Therefore, check if your flight is over a residential property, and follow the rules below.";
"RESIDENTIAL.INFO.C0" = "Your C0 (under 250 g) drone may be flown over uninvolved people, but never over an assembly of people. No minimum distance to housing applies.";
"RESIDENTIAL.INFO.C1" = "Your C1 (under 900 g) drone must never be flown over an assembly of people, and you must not deliberately overfly uninvolved people. If it happens anyway, keep it as brief as possible. No minimum distance to housing applies.";
"RESIDENTIAL.INFO.C2" = "Your C2 (under 4 kg) drone must keep at least 30 m from uninvolved people, or 5 m in low-speed mode, and must not overfly them. This needs the A2 remote pilot certificate.";
"RESIDENTIAL.INFO.C3C4" = "Your C3 or C4 (under 25 kg) drone must keep at least 150 m from residential, commercial, industrial and recreational areas. Over housing that leaves no open-category flight: you would need an operational authorisation in the specific category.";
"RESIDENTIAL.INFO.DK" = "Denmark has an additional rule. You may not fly over an inhabited private property, meaning a house with its fenced or hedged garden or yard, without the occupier's consent, and you must tell them beforehand (§ 19 of the drone bekendtgørelse, BEK 1649). This does not apply if you cross at 100 m or higher and at least 5 m/s, in a straight line on the way somewhere. Breaches are punishable by fine.";
"RESIDENTIAL.INFO.CH" = "Switzerland is not in the EU, but it adopted Regulation 2019/947 unchanged on 1 January 2023 through its air transport agreement with the EU, so the same class limits apply.";

/* Class-specific line appended under a German residential (Wohngrundstück) zone. §21h LuftVO
   grants a sub-250 g exemption here; the EU open-category subcategories (A2/A3) add class-based
   distances on top. */
"DE.RESIDENTIAL.CLASS.C3C4" = "For your C3 or C4 (under 25 kg) drone: open category A3 requires at least 150 m horizontal distance from residential, commercial, industrial and recreational areas. Because it is horizontal, flying higher does not lift it. The §21h ≥100 m exception cannot help here, so overflight is not possible in the open category at any height and needs a specific-category authorisation.";

